############ Notes - Topic 2 #################

# CIS Benchmarks

- Security Benchmark
    - Root users should be disabled
    - sudo should be enabled whenever required
    - Only necessary users should be given sudo priviliedges
    - configure firewalls on network
    - only necessary services are enabled on the server
    - Right permissions are set for files
    - Auditing and logging are enabled on the servers
    - upgrade, patch the servers to prevent from the attacks


- Tools to access the security
    - CIS benchmarking tools, Center for Internet Security
            https://wwww.cisecurity.org/cis-benchmarks

    - CIS-CAT tools : Help in scanning the servers for the benchmarks





############ Notes - Topic 3 #################

# CIS Benchmarks for Kubernetes

    - Register to CIS benchmark website and download the best practices for Kubernetes

    - CIS-CAT Pro* includes support for Kubernetes, CIS-CAT does not include that

    



